<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id52bc82d3-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6" identifier="/us/usc/t28/s1824"><num value="1824">§ 1824.</num><heading> Mileage fees under summons as both witness and juror</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">No constructive or double mileage fees shall be allowed by reason of any person being summoned both as a witness and a juror.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id52bc82d4-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6">(<ref href="/us/act/1948-06-25/ch646">June 25, 1948, ch. 646</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/62/951">62 Stat. 951</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="id52bc82d5-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="historicalAndRevision" id="id52bc82d6-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Historical and Revision Notes</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Based on title 28, U.S.C., 1940 ed., § 602 (<ref href="/us/act/1908-05-27/ch200/s1">May 27, 1908, ch. 200, § 1</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/35/377">35 Stat. 377</ref>).</p>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Words “or as a witness in two or more cases pending in the same court and triable at the same term thereof” were omitted as covered by <ref href="/us/usc/t28/s1821">section 1821 of this title</ref>.</p>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Changes were made in phraseology.</p>
</note>
</notes>
</section>
